sec.p:
To evaluate the validity of the model, the known kinematic values were compared to their corresponding model outputs. Pertaining to ball revolutions, the absolute difference between true rotation rate of the ball (1/


T


) and the modelled rotation rate represented the absolute error of this modelled output. With regard to the spin axis of the ball, the true elevation and azimuth angles were subtracted from their modelled counterparts and made absolute to gauge the modelled error of these variables. Statistical interpretation of the errors was descriptive.
